title: Maryland Zoo hosts online voting on name of newborn giraffe - Baltimore Sun
text:
Maryland Zoo hosts online voting on name of newborn giraffe The Maryland Zoo welcomes a baby giraffe 
The Maryland Zoo in Baltimore announced the birth of a female reticulated giraffe calf. Born on Monday, February 6, 2017, to four-year-old Juma (joo-ma) and eleven-year-old Caesar, this new calf is the first giraffe to be born at the Zoo in over 20 years.

Voters can submit their choice once per day. The winning name will be announced later this week.
